Antwerp 19 sber 1682
mons verhope dat ul behoudelijck sal sijn thuys gecomen desen alleen tot
couver vande ingeslote facture, de welcke gelieft te exomineren ende
d'accoort bevindende vervolgens te amsteren den heere laet het ul wel
geworden waer in ick ul voorderen dienst ien doen gelieft liberlijck de
commanderen, die naer groetenisse blijve
Amst Sam w hulter
In antw: aen ue van 18 deser gelieft voor mij 4 balen van de
conser gementioneerde u welle te doen uyt soeken mits cone
ditit de selve voor sorie segovianae wort verkoght
ten minsten ½ te besprcken tot betalinge omdat ick
die maddelertijt magh sien alsoo ondervinde bij mijn confrat
dat daer fronde in gesciet, waerder beter te bekomen sonde
mij aengenaem sijn prant verlegen ben om een
goede patije goods wollete hebben, toosoria segoviana als
pi2
super fine & segovish wel willende den sprijs geven soo die
het werdich sijn sonde, wat passent vernee geirne
Anvers 22 sber 1682
mons de wed Bernare perrin
mad: puis que le provisions d' huiver, in ont incommode & m'incommodent
iourmeliment, de l'argent iay pris lhardiesse de tirer sur vostre grace
souts 17 courant £100- de goos paijables au mons pierre meurant a 3 sepuain
de veue, valeur reccu de neme, dont ie vous prie de emuser la pouraalite de
cete ma charge & la ar satisfaire a son tems restont assure que vous
pranderay aussi regaro a long temps de mon desbours ne souhaitent, que de
bien servir mes ans et les traiter de maniere de rammais doubter a la
continualite de leur chalandise, ie vous raccommend autre fois loneur de
lettre et ie tacheray de vous te conipenser en tout donnent bon marchez
& de bon marchandise
Aavers 22 sber i682
mons Jaques Bassecourt
mons la prefente, est seulement pour vous adviser la traite passé sur
vostre ce 17 caur en faveur du 6 pr. meurant e £50- e vene, valeu
reccu en conf. du mesme, que je vous pre de la ladis. l sontemp, & los notter
a compte de ceqe van m est reduabl, van priant de gardoner la u d'incomon
que je vouis cent estie, esporte & ne pas maniquer Ebon payen aant
receu jey le dit valeu oultre la neaspte exsteme qui j'ay prsenten
delas
london in henrj maijnard
Antwerp 23 sber 1682
S my last to you was on the 19th courant sence rec: yd of 5 dito by which
Sobserve that you shull provide the desired goods, all which is will, as forthe
pack ila theste to doeked, they areto be dyed hene ted, aurovar or beeu, I doubt
Sshall want 5PF5: yallon mara and wies red maie more: in the meane
while pleaseto dispatch the fine spone cloathes before all, vil them
I desired by ney last and according to the same cullours, you please
to provide an other bale all low prises from 6 to 7 ƒ a yd, & feu
of 7:6 or 8ƒ amonghst them, pray endeavour to send n
lovelij cullours & good goods, & then, I shall be sure to make
to make good prises, I can not for my life patt of many of our
remainders of last yeare though I sold some friday last about 32 p
spanish cloathes, lett the sfamets come the sooner the better and the C12
silver mara alsoo, batt pray endeavour to have shih goods as last yeure
you had from him att £68: the 5 p of 35 a 36 yd, for the where
much bester then these, which came seme and oles wee can have sck
d gerine, 3 am a fraids to loose the customers, wich I should be loast
to do: I told you that my wife was advised & desired to drinck sack, soo
that the liquor I desire is sack, soo one and a haef dousin of battels
I say 18 will be enough of sach which, is a sort of spanish wine much
in demand you knou with you, & no good oneto bead here
london arslear Anmesly
Antwerp: 23 gber 1682
according to my promise of the 16h courant do send you hen
inclosed a bill of £70 sterliux on pierre foissin at 2 uso
for which pleaseto procure the need full & pass to yd awne autt
att 34:9 as soone as more conces in itt shall to be remitted you
whilst I remaine
Brussel Jan Jacops
Antwerp 23 ditto
mons in antwoort aen den ul van 21 deser hebbe gisteren aen ul gesonden in
een gpack twee roij frisaerden, engelst verve
ick wil hopen de selve ul sullen aggreeren daer en tussen soo sijn onse
nortse goederen van brugge herwaerts adroituer versonden, hope de selve int
eynde deser weke hier wesen sullen waer van ul noch sal adviseren blyvende
russel Joseph Sabber son
23 ditto
l
monr in answer to yd of 20 p 27 coarant I have reed the packet you
sent once which shall enamin & pass to yd creditt. I have discoursed n
clay about the bookes, & if to be hadd, you shall have themy first konst
kint told mee his mony was ready, so pray receave that & pres the rest as
much as you can, & in case they de lay seayement, I le thander nith lettres
to spure thuncon, for & wont mony aft brussel & have non here: I shall
take not i0 of yd packets to come & follou yd order non which you
moy depend: you slockings are most all out of their parells, so that the
mint weren mens hose are all one order the otfeer p not to bo desting inshed
as also the black, there beeng no parells togheser butt of which ef made
mention by my formars. in the meane while the mons foust nill sell for
£7:15 or ƒ8 at tasthest the croven, is well black as mint at ƒ5:10
ƒ5:15 bast I doubt non att ƒ6 neither did Jecersels any hugher
so if you please afford mee yd aust most resolution I'El endeavour
to sell then all
Brussel Bernard vanden Clooster
C 23d
desen tot advijs als dat ontfle hebbe t panye enge roode finsaerden van 14 ½ & 15 s
soo ul daer eenige van belieft, hebt maer te comand.. in teerst van de toecomende
weeke sal Ick een partije noortsche goederen hebben, ul connende dinck doen, sal mijn
devoir doen
